# Elite Full-Stack Development Guidelines

## Core Principles
- Production-ready, zero-technical-debt code only
- Clean, readable, self-documenting code with descriptive names
- Follow SOLID/DRY/KISS principles religiously
- No unnecessary abstractions, boilerplate, or speculation
- Security-first approach in all implementations
- Handle all edge cases and errors gracefully
- Performance and scalability considerations in every decision

## Code Quality Standards
- TypeScript strict mode always enabled
- No comments unless absolutely critical (code should be self-documenting)
- Descriptive variable, function, and class names
- Consistent error handling patterns
- Input validation and sanitization everywhere
- Audit trails for all critical operations
- Rate limiting and security headers by default

## Architecture Guidelines
- Modular, maintainable structure
- Clear separation of concerns
- Dependency injection where appropriate
- Service layer for business logic
- Controller layer for HTTP handling
- Middleware for cross-cutting concerns
- Type safety throughout the stack

## Security Requirements
- JWT authentication with proper expiration
- bcrypt for password hashing
- Helmet, CORS, rate limiting enabled
- SQL injection prevention (Prisma ORM)
- XSS protection with input sanitization
- CSRF protection for state-changing operations
- Secure headers and cookie policies

## Database & Data Handling
- Prisma ORM with PostgreSQL
- Proper indexing for performance
- Transactional consistency for financial operations
- Audit logging for all bets and transactions
- Data validation at multiple layers
- Backup and recovery considerations

## API Design
- RESTful principles with consistent patterns
- Proper HTTP status codes
- Standardized error response format
- API versioning consideration
- Comprehensive input validation with Zod
- Rate limiting per endpoint/user

## Frontend Standards
- React 18 with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Responsive, mobile-first design
- Component-based architecture
- State management with Zustand
- Proper error boundaries and loading states
- Accessibility considerations

## Testing & Quality Assurance
- Unit tests for business logic
- Integration tests for API endpoints
- E2E tests for critical user flows
- Code coverage requirements
- Linting and formatting enforcement
- Security scanning in CI/CD

## Performance Requirements
- Optimized database queries
- Efficient state management
- Lazy loading where appropriate
- Image and asset optimization
- Caching strategies implemented
- Monitoring and alerting setup

## Compliance & Legal
- Gambling Control Act 2025 compliance
- Clear warnings about licensing requirements
- Virtual currency only in pilot phase
- KYC/AML considerations for future
- Data privacy regulations adherence
- Terms of service enforcement

## Development Workflow
- Feature branch development
- Code review requirements
- Automated testing in CI/CD
- Staging environment validation
- Production deployment protocols
- Rollback strategies defined

## Monitoring & Observability
- Structured logging with Winston
- Performance metrics collection
- Error tracking and alerting
- User behavior analytics
- System health monitoring
- Security event logging
